  "prompt": "Which songs are best for shrilled voice?",
  "response": "When choosing songs for a shrilled voice, it's important to select pieces that highlight the unique qualities of your vocal range and style. Here are some songs across various genres that are well-suited for a shrilled or high-pitched voice:\n\n### Pop\n1. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston** - This classic ballad requires a powerful high range and emotional delivery.\n2. **\"Since U Been Gone\" by Kelly Clarkson** - Known for its strong, belting chorus that suits a shrilled voice well.\n3. **\"Defying Gravity\" from Wicked** - A challenging song that showcases a high range and dynamic vocal control.\n\n### Rock\n1. **\"Somebody to Love\" by Queen** - Freddie Mercury\u2019s vocal range makes this song perfect for showcasing a high-pitched voice.\n2. **\"Edge of Seventeen\" by Stevie Nicks** - This song has a lot of vocal flair and high notes that can suit a shrilled voice.\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **\"Respect\" by Aretha Franklin** - A powerful song with high belting that can really showcase a shrilled voice.\n2. **\"Chain of Fools\" by Aretha Franklin** - Another classic that allows for a strong vocal performance.\n\n### Musical Theater\n1. **\"Don\u2019t Rain on My Parade\" from Funny Girl** - A show-stopping number that demands a strong, high-pitched voice.\n2. **\"Let It Go\" from Frozen** - This song has become a staple for showcasing high notes and emotional depth.\n\n### Indie/Alternative\n1. **\"The Middle\" by Jimmy Eat World** - The song\u2019s chorus can be a good fit for a shrilled voice, showcasing higher registers.\n2. **\"Sweater Weather\" by The Neighbourhood** - A modern hit that allows for a lot of vocal play in the higher ranges.\n\n### Country\n1. **\"Jolene\" by Dolly Parton** - A classic that highlights a higher-pitched vocal style.\n2. **\"Before He Cheats\" by Carrie Underwood** - A powerful song with a strong, high-pitched chorus.\n\nWhen selecting songs, consider your comfort level with the range and style. It's also helpful to work with a vocal coach who can guide you in choosing songs that best suit your voice and help you perform them effectively.",
